Our family, in three different houses, have rescued 10 black cats over the years. They are the most affectionate and fun cats we have. Any pictures I've taken basically show black lumps, who cares. Take them home, love them and see what you get in return.

I have Teddy Bear, Kenzi, Bear, Salem, Snowball, Storm...plus two more 3 week old kittens Jasper and Peepers, all Bombay mixed breeds. Kenzi, Bear, Salem and Snow are all rescued ferals, now they have a loving home. Bombays are the most loyal, loving, belly-flopping lap-cats. They make an awesome "tribble-like" trilling noise when they get older. I love Bombays more than any other breed. If you have room in your heart, rescue a black cat. They are awesome!
I have two black cats and I agree that they certainly aren't easy to take pictures with but that doesn't mean I am going to abandon them.
